rComments: Don't buy the BIO1530 textbook, you never use it. Easy to do well if you put in the time.
Easy to understand, clear instructions, but many hours of lectures to watch

Superbe prof! Elle explique très bien et semble vraiment passionnée par ce qu'elle enseigne. Elle utilise plusieurs exemples qui aident à bien comprendre. Elle est aussi très accessible et répond à toutes les questions avec grande clarté.

J'ai vraiment apprecié la clarté et l'organisation de Dre. Frechette durant sa classe! Ses présentations sont bien organisés avec l'information importante, et les objectifs d'apprentissage à la début de chaque powerpoint est tout qu'il faut étudier pour réussir aux examens. Sa mode d'explication est aussi très claire!

She is an amazing teacher, I would for sure retake this class if I could. You can easily have a good grade but you have to put in the time and the effort. You can easily pass the class without the textbook (don't waste your money on it).
teacherRatingTags: ['Amazing lectures ', 'Clear grading criteria', 'Get ready to read']

rComments: Exams are unproctored and relevant to her slides + you are given more time than you actually need. She reads the slides during her lectures while also giving good examples and better explanations. The labs were easy. She has 3 ways of calculating your grade and will pick whichever gives you the best grade, which is nice.
I got Pr. Frechette for BIO1530 (an asynchronous class) and she talks at a perfect rate for note taking. Also, she is a really caring Professor and wants you to understand. Loved her!

All her lectures were done by video, they included lots of real-life examples. The midterms were optional, as she took the best combination of midterms and final, so you can get the best grade possible. You could ask questions by email or discussion forum. She seemed to care about the students while answering questions.

Probably my favorite prof so far in first year. Such a lovely person, and so passionate about what she's teaching. She's extremely accessible when it comes to questions, and her lectures and slides are very clear/well formatted, and engaging.

Frechette was a great prof for first year bio. She reads her slides, but gave good explanations. She is clearly passionate about biology and transfers this energy to her students. Two midterms and a final reflected course materials and as long as you watched her videos, doing well comes naturally. Pick her if you have the choice.

To be honest this prof is really awesome. I am in Bio 1130 but follow her classes froma friend. She is a really good prof and her notes are so perfect, well organised and explains the concepts very well. I wish I took her class instead of the english one with Prof Rundle and Delcourt where it's pretty much atrocious. Her class really kept me going

This was her first year teaching BIO1530 and she was great. I put like 0% effort in this class, just listen to her asynchronous lectures on 1.5x speed and youre fine. She speaks very clearly and gives many examples to help with comprehension, and the exams are fairly easy if you watched the lectures. Shes very organized and clearly loves nature!

Good at teaching the concepts and is very clear about what's on the exam/quiz. Tests are open book but you cant pass without studying and understanding the concepts. If you're aiming for a 60-70, you should be fine if you go to all the classes and study hardcore the day before. To get a good grade (80-90) you need to study for at least 2-3 days.

the class is very interesting and she tries to make it dynamic with exemples , still i think her lecturing isnt great (she just reads the slides most of the time and i dont find that the info she adds on top of whats writtent is useful or helps you understand)but considering its her first time teaching the class id say she did ok

Elle a pris beaucoup de temps pour bien expliquer le cours, car il y a beaucoup d'informations nouvelles à mémoriser. les tests sont longs, mais pas difficiles si on a bien étudié. elle prends soin de ses étudiants. très bonne prof et un très bon cours si y met son effort.
Nouvelle prof donc peu d'expérience en enseignement mais j'ai tout de même beaucoup aimé le cours. Elle se souci de la compréhension et des questions de ses étudiants :)
